sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Admin User
    participant Angular as Angular Frontend
    participant BE as Backend API
    participant OAuth as Google OAuth
    participant DB as Database
    participant Storage as Minio/Azure Storage
    
    rect rgb(200, 220, 255)
    Note over User,DB: Authentication Flow
    User->>Angular: 1. Click "Sign in with Google"
    Angular->>BE: 2. GET /auth/login
    BE->>OAuth: 3. Redirect to Google OAuth
    OAuth-->>User: 4. Show consent screen
    User->>OAuth: 5. Approve
    OAuth->>BE: 6. Redirect to /auth/google-callback with code
    BE->>OAuth: 7. Exchange code for token
    OAuth-->>BE: 8. Return access token
    BE->>OAuth: 9. GET user info (email, sub)
    OAuth-->>BE: 10. Return user info
    BE->>DB: 11. Find/Create user in database
    DB-->>BE: 12. User record
    BE->>DB: 13. Assign Admin role (if email matches config)
    DB-->>BE: 14. Role assigned
    BE->>BE: 15. Generate JWT token
    BE-->>Angular: 16. Redirect to /dashboard?token=JWT
    Angular->>Angular: 17. Store JWT in localStorage
    end
    
    rect rgb(200, 255, 200)
    Note over Angular,Storage: Album Creation & Photo Upload
    User->>Angular: 18. Fill album form & submit
    Angular->>BE: 19. POST /api/albums (JWT in header)
    BE->>BE: 20. Verify JWT, extract user claims
    BE->>DB: 21. Create Album entity
    DB-->>BE: 22. Album created with ID
    BE-->>Angular: 23. Return album JSON
    Angular-->>User: 24. Show album created, redirect to upload
    User->>Angular: 25. Select photos for upload
    Angular->>BE: 26. POST /api/albums/{id}/photos (multipart)
    BE->>Storage: 27. Upload original photo
    Storage-->>BE: 28. Return storage key
    BE->>DB: 29. Create Photo record
    DB-->>BE: 30. Photo saved
    BE->>BE: 31. Queue image processing
    BE-->>Angular: 32. Return photo JSON
    end
    
    rect rgb(255, 220, 200)
    Note over BE,Storage: Image Processing (background)
    BE->>Storage: 33. GET original photo
    Storage-->>BE: 34. Download original
    BE->>BE: 35. Compress (4 versions: High/Med/Low/Raw)
    BE->>Storage: 36. Upload high-quality version
    BE->>Storage: 37. Upload med-quality version
    BE->>Storage: 38. Upload low-quality version
    BE->>Storage: 39. Upload raw version
    BE->>DB: 40. Create PhotoVersion records
    DB-->>BE: 41. Versions saved
    end
    
    rect rgb(255, 255, 200)
    Note over User,DB: Access Code Generation
    User->>Angular: 42. Create 30-day access code
    Angular->>BE: 23. POST /api/albums/{id}/access-codes (expirationDays: 30)
    BE->>DB: 44. Create AccessCode (expires in 30 days)
    DB-->>BE: 45. Code created (code: "ABC123XY")
    BE-->>Angular: 46. Return access code
    Angular-->>User: 47. Show code to share
    end
    
    rect rgb(200, 255, 255)
    Note over User,Storage: Visitor Access via Code
    participant Visitor as Client/Visitor
    Visitor->>Angular: 48. Enter access code
    Angular->>BE: 49. POST /code/validate?code=ABC123XY
    BE->>DB: 50. Find AccessCode, check expiration
    DB-->>BE: 51. Code is valid
    BE->>BE: 52. Generate visitor JWT token
    BE-->>Angular: 53. Return album + visitor token
    Angular-->>Visitor: 54. Show album & photos
    Visitor->>Angular: 55. Click download photo
    Angular->>BE: 56. GET /code/{code}/photo/{id}/download?quality=high (visitor JWT)
    BE->>Storage: 57. GET high-quality version
    Storage-->>BE: 58. Return file
    BE-->>Angular: 59. Return file to browser
    Angular-->>Visitor: 60. Browser downloads photo
    end
